<@U12452RAP> - right - well I assumed that within the SDKs we were enrolling clients (not TLS servers, etc) and therefore we need only put the enrollID in the subject DN.    I also intentionally did not add in being able to specify profile, etc as frankly I don't think that people using the client SDKs should be doing that.  My assumption would be that COP would be setup with the profile that they COP admin wanted.   

But you'll notice that it would be trivially to add it in - I just did not see the requirement to do it now and wanted to keep things as simple as possible

could someone take a look at <https://jenkins.hyperledger.org/view/fabric/job/fabric-verify-node-sdk-x86_64/133/console> and <https://jenkins.hyperledger.org/view/fabric/job/fabric-merge-node-sdk-x86_64/34/console> and tell me if this is something I need to correct in the minion, or if it is an error in the code itself?
<@U0UHG4VP1|ry> uploaded a file: <https://hyperledgerproject.slack.com/files/ry/F3PPGPWLT/this_is_the_actual_error.txt|this is the actual error>
